headline: Centene's Q2 loss: Why health insurers face such big headwinds
summary: Health insurers are navigating rising costs and regulatory challenges, with Centene (CNC) slashing its forecast amid ACA uncertainties. Arthur Wong, S&P Global Ratings healthcare managing director, and Adriel Bettelheim, Axios senior healthcare editor, discuss the impact on the industry and what's ahead.
